===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|尸|𧝑|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|abb2=y}}, which has a variant [[𧝣]]; the original version is [[㞡]]. The phonetic component is a reference to fine red silk clothes, one of the six garments worn by the queen in the Rites of Zhou, and it contains as well a reference to the concept of "opening, extending; watch carefully" in the component [[㠭]].

Similar but unrelated to [[昔]] and [[共]].

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-dal||[[spread]]; [[extend]]; [[develop]]}} (STEDT).

